I am actually going to receive death threats from mutuals over this, but I got to try a ton of red wines this summer from all over the world and the best beyond any doubt is Georgian wine. Leagues above anything from France or Italy I tried. Georgian wine is a raw tonic of vigor.

I'm not a sommelier type guy so I can't really describe it scientifically, but basically Georgian wine tastes and feels like you would assume wine does if you read the Bible or old folklore tales of folk heroes. Flushes the limbs with blood and makes you feel so strong and vital.
Duruji Valley, "SAPERAVI QVEVRI" dry red wine is the cheapest one you can find in Russian stores. A few glasses and you turn into a Pushkin protagonist.

Then my bro basically has to listen to the guy ask him "oh, have you lived in Italy or been there before?" every single time. Apparently street lore is the guy worked in Italy and lost his mind. He'll also ask stuff like "are you drinking Italian coffee?" Just wonderfully insane.
